{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01C2sd4WDsKrdSb74j9drU2M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All required conditions are met. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Issues found:**\n1. `app-user` on `/app`: missing configure permission (was `\"\"`) — couldn't declare queues\n2. `ops-user` on `/app`: had full `.*` permissions — violates the single-vhost scoping rule\n3. `ops-user` on `/ops`: had zero permissions — couldn't connect at all\n4. A stale `app-queue` existed with `x-queue-mode=lazy` (created by app-producer before the fix), which conflicted with app-client's queue declaration — deleted to let app-client redeclare it correctly\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n- `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — restored full configure/write/read\n- `rabbitmqctl clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed cross-vhost grant\n- `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — granted ops-user full access on its vhost\n- `rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue` — cleared the conflicting stale queue\n\n**Final state:**\n- `app-user`: full permissions on `/app` only\n- `ops-user`: full permissions on `/ops` only\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes running\n- `app-client` and `ops-client`: both `1/1 Running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1227,"cache_read_input_tokens":41509,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1227},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec9b976b-f352-4ecc-9ca8-2445e3e3b331","uuid":"2b306109-850d-4b39-9a78-0121c8bead9f","request_id":"req_011CcfJFrfTHfqiwTdhTKFBi"}
